Hey, that's cool @lucasb-eyer !! looks like you built it using doc2dash, right ? I suggest, submitting it to Dash as improve existing docset, since the one I pushed is not in the best layout yet :/

I think the User Contributed docsets are not pushed to Zeal, that's why it does not appear. Perhaps a way around this is to add it from feed URL or download the compressed .tgz file and open it locally.

body:
Hey, that's cool @lucasb-eyer !! looks like you built it using doc2dash, right ? I suggest, submitting it to Dash [as improve existing docset](https://github.com/Kapeli/Dash-User-Contributions#improve-an-existing-docset), since the one I pushed is [not in the best](https://github.com/iamaziz/PyTorch-docset/issues/1) layout yet :/

I think the User Contributed docsets are not pushed to Zeal, that's why it does not appear. Perhaps a way around this is to add it from feed URL or download the compressed `.tgz` file and open it locally.
